<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4024&amp;p=4719#p4719"><![CDATA[
Except in Firefox in standards mode, you can do <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;p id='foo'&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;script&gt;<br /> foo.innerHTML = 'Hello World'<br />&lt;/script&gt;</code></dd></dl><br />Or you could use Selectors API to easily target the element you want without cluttering the markup with attributes:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>document.querySelector&#40;'#section1 &gt; p:first-of-type'&#41;.innerHTML = 'Hello World'</code></dd></dl><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Wed Oct 29, 2008 12:11 pm</p><hr />
